sections.title: How the population has changed in Sevenoaks
sections.label: Select another area to see how the population has changed

sections.content: In 2020, Sevenoaks was the 40th largest local authority in the South East, with a total population of 121,387. An increase compared with 2019.

sections.title: Largest local authorities in the South East, 2002-2020
Population density in Sevenoaks
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in Sevenoaks was 329 people per square kilometre, which was less than the South East (483), and more than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Densest local authorities in the South East, 2020
Median age in Sevenoaks
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in Sevenoaks was 44 years, which was older than the South East (42 years), and older than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
